00:03:09.291 --> 00:03:11.757
it would be times U of X.

00:03:11.757 --> 00:03:12.840
Times U of X.

00:03:14.397 --> 00:03:16.320
And of course, that whole thing

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:17.903
times U prime of X.

00:03:19.695 --> 00:03:22.208
And so, and I'm doing
more steps just hopefully

00:03:22.208 --> 00:03:23.943
so it's clearer what I'm doing here.

00:03:23.943 --> 00:03:25.528
So this is one over

00:03:25.528 --> 00:03:27.998
the natural log of four.

00:03:27.998 --> 00:03:30.248
U of X is X squared plus X.

00:03:31.219 --> 00:03:32.612
So

00:03:32.612 --> 00:03:34.029
X squared plus X.

00:03:35.072 --> 00:03:36.079
And then we're gonna multiply that

00:03:36.079 --> 00:03:37.246
times U prime of X.

00:03:37.246 --> 00:03:39.385
So times two X plus one.

00:03:39.385 --> 00:03:41.162
And so we can just rewrite this as

00:03:41.162 --> 00:03:42.745
two X plus one over

00:03:45.296 --> 00:03:46.129
over

00:03:47.747 --> 00:03:49.017
over

00:03:49.017 --> 00:03:50.745
the natural log of four.

00:03:50.745 --> 00:03:52.863
The natural log of four

00:03:52.863 --> 00:03:54.780
times X squared plus X.

00:03:55.617 --> 00:03:56.867
Times X squared

00:03:58.962 --> 00:03:59.795
plus X.

00:03:59.795 --> 00:04:00.867
And we're done, and we could distribute

00:04:00.867 --> 00:04:02.143
this natural log of four

00:04:02.143 --> 00:04:03.650
if we found that interesting.

00:04:03.650 --> 00:04:06.010
But, we have just found
the derivative of Y

00:04:06.010 --> 00:04:07.593
